The cabinet shall establish additional requirements for the approval of instructors, including but not limited to the following:
The person shall have a high school diploma or its equivalent;
The person shall be at least eighteen (18) years of age and hold a valid motorcycle driver's license or endorsement;
The person shall have at least two (2) years of recent motorcycle riding experience;
The person's driver's license shall not have been suspended or revoked at any time during the preceding two (2) years or at any time within the preceding five (5) years for any alcohol or drug related offense; and
The person shall not have been convicted of a felony.
